sec.p:
Federal Magistrate Smith did not accept that Australia Post had discharged this onus. Despite arguments submitted by Australia Post that Mr Brennan, the person who made the decision to terminate the employee, based his consideration only on the two factors outlined in the letter of termination dated 7 January 2010, Smith FM stated that this evidence was difficult to accept given:


the doubts as to Mr Brennan’s credibility as a witness and the reliability of his evidence (he had a poor memory and guarded presentation when questioned at trial);

the almost total lack of contemporaneous documentation as to the investigations and deliberations leading to the decision;

the unexplained unfairness in terms of the procedures implemented;

the disproportionate nature of the decision; and

the unexplained failure of Australia Post to call a significant witness from its human resources department who advised the decision-maker.
